I feel like this is a ballsy, and relatively well-executed, attempt at a first! If It had to criticize anything it would be a one of the things you added to try and demonstrate how technologically advanced this civilization was.

While the vertical farming bit seems neat, even modern attempts at vertical farming are hindered by problems of economic viability/efficiency and quantitative output. The lighting problem is also fairly challenging even with modern technology like high efficiency LEDs. Mirrors can't actually solve this problem for you since they only reflect the amount of light that actually strikes its small surface (it's also worth mentioning that the sun is a pain since it changes angles on you throughout the day), and for lack of a focusing mechanism there would be substantial losses for each subsequent reflection on top of that (which is why that famous scene in  with the mirrors is b.s).







